<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,222,535]" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,402,427]" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[563,692,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">Ampelornis</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[753,887,402,427]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">Poliocrania</emphasis>
by female throat spots and loudsong structure. Further distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[457,591,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">Poliocrania</emphasis>
by nest structure and lack of blue periorbital patch and from 
<emphasis box="[1272,1401,438,463]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="489">Ampelornis</emphasis>
by numerous morphometric measures, such as tail length/wing length ratio; differences in foraging behavior supportive.
</paragraph>
